I have no interest in befriending the type of “Christians” who have the perfect life, the highlight reel everyone envy’s, and who act like they don’t struggle. The type that act like their life is perfect because they go to church every Sunday and some preacher told them they were perfect. No. I don’t want those kinds of people in my life. You see, I don’t have anything in common with those people. I am a Christian who struggles everyday to pick up and carry my cross. I struggle everyday to forgive myself and others sometimes. I struggle with sin that I hate but seem to slip back into. And even on my BEST days I know I need Jesus more than anything. I want the type of people around me who are just as broken and imperfect as me but who are trying their hardest everyday to love others and be kind and accepting. The kind of people who have compassion when someone misses the mark and to love others when they can’t love themselves. To be understanding that everyone’s walk with Christ may not look like their own. Jesus said they will know you by your LOVE. Not your judgements, not your condescending looks, and not by your condemnation. But by your love. 
Love those who hurt you, love those who need love, and be kind. That is the type of Christian I want to be. And it’s not easy… its hard. But when you ask God to soften your heart everyday, you start to see a shift in the way you respond to things and others, it’s really a beautiful thing… trying to unlearn everything the world has taught me and go against the grain, that’s what He did. 
.
.

I have always loved bodybuilding. It was an area in my life that not only saved me, but it was an area I found that I was very good at. With that being said, bodybuilding is a constant state of learning! 
You’re goal while bodybuilding shouldn’t be just to get BIG, but to improve, to learn your body, push through weaknesses, and improve your self physically and mentally. Building muscle on the upper half of my body came pretty easy for me. Building a BALANCED lower body was not easy for me.
 I am quad dominate and my glutes never seemed to engage or grow. UNTIL, I learned how to practice Mind Muscle Connection. Not just going through the motions of the lift, but really focusing in my mind what muscles I was using in the lift and squeezing the proper muscles at the right time. 
This slowed down my movements, really made me focus on the range of motion, and engage each muscle properly. I was quickly humbled by the decrease in weight but realized that I could get more out of my lift with less weight and better reps.
 I wouldn’t consider myself an expert but I do have quite a bit experience in building so do with this info what you would like :) happy 🍑 building.

In a world that screams self love and healing and doing it all on your own…I haven’t met many people who actually have been able to heal themselves truthfully. They’re smiling but they’re still hurting or have scars from past hurt. Putting concealer on is the same as pretending the wound isn’t there. Might work for a little while- but at the end of the night you have to wash off the mask and face the truth.  I would be bold face lying to you if I told you that God has healed me from my pain and emotional wounds. But what He has done, is given me strength DESPITE my weaknesses. Don’t be ashamed of your scars and your wounds and imperfections, find strength from them. Find the lessons behind them. Find the ways to change someone’s life because of what you’ve learned before it’s too late for them. I know this is a hard concept to grasp. But it’s having the humility to not dwell where you are. It’s hard not to do that in our type of world and culture. But it’s worth it if you can see the beauty that comes after the rain. 
.
.

Mother’s Day is coming up soon and this post is for the moms only. (You’ll get your post on Father’s Day dads 👌🏼) 
Can we just take a minute and possibly agree on something? That this instagram “perfect mom” aesthetic is… fake. And it’s so damn annoying! Pretending that we’re happy all the time, that our kids never act bipolar twelve times a day, and that we are always perfectly put together with our makeup done and sporting the latest fashion trends. I don’t know about y’all, but I can’t keep up, and I don’t care to 😂 
Being a mom is a freaking roller coaster 🎢 The only time I look fully put together is when I don’t have my kid! 😂 we make sure they have everything they need, look their best, feel their best, and we take a back seat WILLINGLY. 
My home is not painted in beautiful nude colors with accent pictures and flowers, the beds are half made, I have mix matched drawings and colorings all over the place displayed, and I guarantee I’ve washed the same load of laundry 3 times already because I forgot about it. My hair is a mess 90% of the time and I’m probably the grungiest parent in the morning dropping their kid off at school because I’ve only had one cup of coffee and hit snooze too many times. But you know what?! My kid is happy, he’s in love with me, he loves our life, and he’s got everything he needs! 
And that’s what the goal is. Not getting the approval of other moms on IG or fitting in to the look of what the modern mom looks like. We do our best and that’s what matters. Especially when we do it all alone. Cheers to you!

Y’all… it’s tough a hell out here!! Everyone’s offended, everyone’s entitled, everyone living in their made up fantasy world where they don’t claim their own biology, people a(bort-ing) just because it’s their “right”, everyone going with the flow and afraid to speak out because they don’t want to get cancelled…😅 everyday it’s something new! And if you’re a Christian?! They’ll say you’re the worst of them all! Heaven forbid your a Christian who speaks out… like you’re SUPPOSED to! 
It would be soooo much easier to call myself a Christian and sit back and do absolutely nothing God tells me to do, affirm everyone’s opinion and beliefs, and live my life in a way that only serves me and brings me comfort. So easy. And no one would say a word to me and everyone would like me. Cause I kept my mouth shut and my “religion” quiet. 
Well, hate to break it to ya, but I’m not gonna do any of that. As true Christians we are called to be in the world but not of it. That means we are here to gather who we can but we don’t stay here and we don’t live by the world. We openly invite persecution because if we’re being persecuted then we know we’re doing exactly what God told us. He said we will be persecuted. 
“Blessed are those who are persecuted for righteousness’ sake, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.” -Matthew 5:10 
People who go against God and do evil in this world are so stead fast and strong in their mission. So why shouldn’t we be?! Do not let the world dim your light and scare you from speaking with the authority God gave you. Evil will never stop and it’s about time they got a taste of God people. Combat hate with love. Pray hard for those who wrong you and refuse to see their sin. Speak the name of Jesus even when you know you’re outnumbered. Keep your nose in your Bible, it will tell you what to do, and tell you what is coming! And don’t ever lose your faith! 🙏🏼 

Please share this message!

So since no one else wants to say it…Everyone wants to preach the feel good parts of the gospel and the Bible but no one wants to talk about confronting your sin or challenge how you live your life. Why? Cause they’re afraid of hurting your feelings or getting cancelled. But listen, God didn’t send Jesus down here to make people “feel good”. He came to let you know that there are two ways! ONLY two. There is the path to eternal life, and there is the path to eternal hell. 
I posted a story awhile ago that perfectly illustrated those two paths: There’s a boy sitting on a fence between two fields. On one side of the fence is God, on the other side of the fence is Satan. The world ends and God leaves, and satan leaves. But then Satan comes back to the boy and says “almost forgot, you’re coming with me.” The boy replies, “whoa whoa, I didn’t choose God and i certainly didn’t choose you.” The devil says back to him, “the fence is mine.”
Almost everyone I know argued with me that the fence was neutral zone because they hadn’t decided or they didn’t know enough to make their choice. Thats EXACTLY what Satan wants you to think and feel. If you’re still on the fence, he’s got you. If you’re not choosing God, you’re choosing yourself, the world, and your sin that you’ve gotten so comfortable with. 
Gods way is narrow and hard and that’s why he says few will make it! But the easy way is broad, paved, and many are walking it, but it won’t lead to heaven. 
Sin is sin. There is no grey area, there is no justification for it. If the Bible says it’s a sin, our opinions dont matter. We all do it. We’re both going to do it till the day we take out last breath. No person is perfect, no Christian is perfect! But you have to make efforts to stay away from those sins and ask for forgiveness when they happen. We have no idea what day we will draw our last breath. You might think you’re healthy as an ox today but anything could happen tomorrow! 
I don’t say all this to shove it down your throat, or to condemn you. I would be condemning myself also. But if you love someone, you pull them from the fire, you don’t watch them burn! Choose the road less traveled. Seek and you will find.

Recently had the pleasure of meeting Dr. Chase Carlin who is a chiropractor in the Lenexa area. I don’t post this kinda stuff often but I cannot say enough great things about him! He listened well to my history, took my sport injuries seriously, and was very thorough! 
I hadn’t been to the chiropractor in a few years, nursed my own injuries at home or learned to cope with them because I felt like no one would actually listen to how I was feeling, or they would just do the routine neck and back adjustment and send me on my way. Not this guy! I was able to be adjusted in places I around my shoulder blades, traps, lower back, hips, ankles, feet, and neck! 
I’m sleeping better, have more mobility in my neck and hips, and less headaches! I was able to do my first round of acupuncture today for the first time and it was an awesome experience! He made it painless, he explained what he was doing throughout the process, and told me what to expect during and after. I carry a lot of tension in my shoulders and neck, and I have a injured left shoulder that gives out when I’m lifting. Immediately we were able to get more blood flow into those areas and I felt alot of tension and tightness subside. Really excited for my next visit to keep progressing. 
If you’re in the Kansas City, Overland Park, or Lenexa area I HIGHLY recommend checking Carlin Chiropractic out. I truly believe you won’t be disappointed! Tell him I sent you!

I have to share this sweet moment because as a single mom, I just cannot contain the amount of love in my heart tonight. I got my son back tonight after what seemed like the longest and most emotional week. I am very positive and strong when I have him and I tend to get very depressed and mentally weak when I’m alone. He was such a great helper this evening, cooking dinner with me and helping me get everything ready. He showered me with compliments as a mother, told me over and over how much he loved me and how thankful he was that we have each other. It took everything in me not to just break down and cry from the overloaded of raw love and emotion I felt. He had absolutely no idea the week I had been through or how badly I had missed him but he must have known I just needed him. Or maybe he needed me the same way. 

Our kids are our kids for a reason. I truly believe God gives you the child you need. The one who heals the broken parts of you, the one who brings out the best in you, the one who makes you want to step up and be the best parent you can be. I have absolutely no idea how I will love another child the way I love him. He shows me everyday what true and unconditional love is. 
I challenge you to go to your child tonight (if you can, or next time you see them) and look them dead in the eyes and tell them how much you appreciate them. And then watch them melt in love for you! There is nothing better. 
So to my son, thanks for making me feel like I belong here and that I’m needed still. ❤️ 
#love #motherhood #boymom

It really doesn’t feel like I’ve had a child as long as I have. I feel like time has flown faster than I thought it would. 8 years ago I was freshly in my 20’s and learning everything about being a parent for the first time. My son and I have the best bond and relationship, better than I would have imagined, and I am proud of the mother I have been and still becoming! We teach our children all the things in life and how to navigate their way through the world each year. Milestone by milestone. We never really stop to realize how many milestones were reaching ourselves. We’re becoming more patient, more loving, more sacrificial, more empathetic, and less and less about ourselves. I know this world screams “self-everything”, but I think we can take that too far. 
My point is- it’s OK to look back at how far you’ve come as a parent or realize how long you’ve been parenting and be proud of that! It’s OK to say you’re doing a hell of a job! God gives us grace everyday, give yourself some grace too. If people want to say you’re “bragging”, let them. But at what point in life are we allowed to give ourselves a pat on the back and be positive about something for once?! I’d say NOW. 

#parenting #kids #growingup #adulting #fyp #boss #proud #grace #feelinggood #experience

I’ll never forget being a little girl and feeling so alone and so unwanted by the people who were supposed to love and protect me. It’s a feeling that has stayed with me well into adulthood unfortunately. But I’m not sorry for myself. I’m thankful for having felt that because I promised myself that when I had kids they would never question wether they were loved or wanted or needed or valued. They would just know because of how their mother treated them. People ask me why I’m so protective of my son… I’m making sure he doesn’t have to recover from his childhood. And I make no apologies about how I do that. Empathy is a very powerful thing… it runs very deep. If you can realize why people do things the way they do, or fear the things they fear, you’d understand so much more about them and spend way less time judging or fighting them.

The one thing people don’t tell you about their recovery from substance abuse is that the urges don’t disappear forever. Triggers bring back familiar feelings and memories and then the urge to self soothe comes back with it as well. You want to feel numb, you want to disappear, you want to escape reality just one more time…but you don’t. You feel it… all of it and then you fight it. You remind yourself how far you’ve come and all you have to lose. You remember that with pain comes perseverance and hope. Pain effects us all differently. For me- I’ve always been a runner. I want to escape it and avoid it and protect myself from it. But as I get older, I’m learning that pain has made the best parts of me. It’s made me strong, it’s given me empathy, it’s allowed me to be merciful, and it’s a hell of a motivator!
If you’re in recovery, I commend you for another day. A lot of people don’t understand the silent battles we fight. #recovery #sober #reslience #fyp #mentalhealthawareness

1- The only real affirmation you need, is from yourself. But by depriving yourself of affirmation and positive self talk, you continue to self sabotage and feel empty. So you continue to hope it will come from others. 
2- Continuing to be kind and loving when others around you are being negative and hurtful will eventually become a habit and seem like a superpower after awhile. Sure, it’ll probably trigger those around you who don’t know how to receive kindness or love when they’re angry.. but they’ll never forget that you may have been the one person who showed them love during that time. 
3- Sometimes the truth WILL hurt. Real honesty is painful. To tell or to receive. But it’s absolutely essential for growth. For you and everyone around you. Embrace that you’re not always right and you’re going to have traits about you that need work. Appreciate the people who are willing to bring those things to your attention to help you grow and succeed. Just cause it may hurt to hear doesn’t mean it was said without love.
